            "mimeType": "application/json; charset=UTF-8",
            "size": 1030,
            "text": "{\n  \"candidates\": [\n    {\n      \"content\": {\n        \"parts\": [\n          {\n            \"text\": \"**My Plan to Get the Temperature Information**\\n\\nOkay, so the user needs the current temperature in Paris and London. Seems straightforward. I can definitely handle this. My immediate thought is to utilize the `get_current_temperature` tool. I know how to use it; I've used it many times before. The process is simple: I'll call the tool once, specifying \\\"Paris\\\" as the city. Then, I'll call it again, but this time with \\\"London\\\". That should give me the two temperature readings that I need, and then I can present them to the user. No problem!\\n\",\n            \"thought\": true\n          },\n          {\n            \"functionCall\": {\n              \"name\": \"get_current_temperature\",\n              \"args\": {\n                \"city\": \"Paris\"\n              }\n            },\n            \"thoughtSignature\": \"\"\n          },\n          {\n            \"functionCall\": {\n              \"name\": \"get_current_temperature\",\n              \"args\": {\n                \"city\": \"London\"\n              }\n            }\n          }\n        ],\n        \"role\": \"model\"\n      },\n      \"finishReason\": \"STOP\",\n      \"index\": 0,\n      \"finishMessage\": \"Model generated function call(s).\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"usageMetadata\": {\n    \"promptTokenCount\": 61,\n    \"candidatesTokenCount\": 34,\n    \"totalTokenCount\": 145,\n    \"promptTokensDetails\": [\n      {\n        \"modality\": \"TEXT\",\n        \"tokenCount\": 61\n      }\n    ],\n    \"thoughtsTokenCount\": 50,\n    \"serviceTier\": \"standard\"\n  },\n  \"modelVersion\": \"gemini-2.5-flash\",\n  \"responseId\": \"_wUVaoSfK8X9jrEPzduyiAE\"\n}\n"
